When I looked it up I sort of expected it, but actually seeing it on the Apple Store page makes me shake my head.

Lenovo Laptop in question:

https://www.bestbuy.com/site/lenovo-yoga-c930-2-in-1-13-9-4k-ultra-hd-touch-screen-laptop-intel-core-i7-16gb-memory-512gb-solid-state-drive-mica/6295987.p?skuId=6295987

MacBook Pro Laptop Equivalent:

https://www.apple.com/shop/buy-mac/macbook-pro/15-inch

The MacBook does have discrete graphics and the 6-core i7 model as opposed to the 4-core one, but the price still isn't justified. Here's a faster equivalent MacBook Pro (with a GTX 1060 and the same 6-core processor) for $1,100 less:

https://smile.amazon.com/GIGABYTE-Aero-15X-v8-BK4-Anti-Glare/dp/B07BSXCCHK/

You see guys. I was balls deep in puts last weekend. BALLS DEEP. Futures opened and we went -350. Pure ducking joy. Then trump ripped my tendies away. I learned my lesson this week, especially with the holiday, traders coming back from vacation, stimulus from EU and the Fed upcoming weeks, Fed buying Treasuries again, and bought HD and SPY calls Friday EOD. Inversing the universe to make a buck. Lets fucking go.

You can beat the market you just need enough bullets (liquid) to keep firing when playing options.

Problem is Hedge funds have a truck ton of bullets.

I go on a 4-5 miss streak on doubling down I’m fucked.

Case in point I played earnings this summer. Small play on ROKU puts....lost

Doubled down on HD puts.... lost

Quadrupled down on TGT calls... backed up the brinks truck. And I’m positive 6K even after taking those 2 losses in a row.

Hit big on TGT and then reverted back to a smaller investment on CRM earnings and got a decent return.

I’m essentially applying the Martingale betting system to earnings and its paying off. Just keep doubling down, I’ve never been a lucky person when it comes to gambling but do your research and honestly just hitting 1/3 big earnings events will beat the market average in my opinion.

Don’t make plays just to make them. Look for big events like earnings, and flip a coin. Just hope you don’t lose 5 in a row.

Here’s a freebie September 17th play SPY puts I don’t think the fed cuts rates or at worst .25BPS. Market is pricing in .5 or better. You’ll see a nice 2% drop after the meeting.

Pick and choose your moves. Best practice is to just make 4-5 moves a month in my opinion. If you’re one of these autists that just has to have skin in the game you’re gonna lose to Theta.
